# 📊 Key Insights — Diabetes Risk Analysis

## Finding 1 — Overall Diabetes Rate
- 34.9% of patients are diabetic
- 65.1% of patients are healthy

## Finding 2 — Top Risk Factors
1. Glucose level (most important)
2. BMI (second most important)
3. Age (third most important)

## Finding 3 — Age Group Analysis
- Senior (45-60): 58% diabetes rate
- Elderly (60+): 50% diabetes rate
- Middle Age (30-45): 45% diabetes rate
- Young (under 30): 22% diabetes rate

## Finding 4 — High Risk Zone
- Patients with Glucose > 140 AND BMI > 30
  are 3x more likely to be diabetic

## Finding 5 — ML Model Performance
- Logistic Regression: 79% accuracy
- Decision Tree: 77% accuracy
- Best predictor: Glucose level
